== Haikufire replacement cannidate

A rewrite of Haikufire.com in Rails to simplify the management of the site.
Rails should make development much easier and make things easier to keep up with.

I am new to Rails/Ruby... so be kind :)


== Rails Environment Setup

* Clean up
** uninstall all ruby versions and gems if previously installed
* Install needed libraries ( you WILL need these ;) )
** sudo apt-get install libssl-dev zlib-dev libmagickcore-dev libmagickwand-dev sqlite3 libsqlite3-dev libreadline-dev
* Setup ruby environment
** install rvm system-wide
** add user to rvm group
** add rvm bits to .bashrc
** logout, login
** open a shell
** rvm install 1.9.2
** rvm use 1.9.2
* Install Rails 3 gem into Ruby 1.9.2 environment
** gem install rails
